{
  "texts": [
    "Derived from censuses, models and remote sensing applications 26, they define the dates for different stages of crop cultivation, including planting and harvest.",
    "Among other uses, crop calendars are mainly utilized when monitoring crop conditions, forecasting and estimating crop yields, and monitoring crop conditions 27.",
    "Existing crop calendars with global coverage",
    "The production of crops, livestock and aquatic organisms covers more than a third of land 1, 2 and oceans 3, altering Earth systems 4 and influencing human health and well-being 5.",
    "Food production has a central role in determining the extent to which nations can achieve UN Sustainable Development Goal (SDG) targets 6, including SDG2 -Zero Hunger."
  ]
}